summary: This is an email from the Eastern District of New York (EDNY) forwarding a phone call from a potential witness in the Epstein case. The witness specifically wanted to speak to someone from the U.S. Attorney's Office (USAO) and, after failing to reach the Southern District of New York (SDNY), called the EDNY. An EDNY investigator documented the call, and the matter was referred to the SDNY.

events.title: Potential Witness Contacts EDNY
events.description: A potential witness in the Epstein case called the Eastern District of New York, stating he only wished to speak to someone from the U.S. Attorney's Office. After failing to reach the SDNY, he contacted the EDNY.

keyFacts: A potential witness in the Epstein case contacted the Eastern District of New York on July 9, 2019.
The witness specifically requested to speak only to someone from the U.S. Attorney's Office.
The witness had previously tried and failed to contact the Southern District of New York.
An EDNY investigator documented the call in a Memorandum of Interview.
The EDNY referred the matter to the SDNY, indicating an SDNY investigator might contact the witness.
